# Project memory: append short, independent bullet lines (see CLAUDE.md).
# `union` is a built-in merge driver: on conflict it keeps the additions from
# BOTH sides instead of writing conflict markers — ideal for an append-only
# memory file edited from parallel worktrees. (Occasional duplicate line is the
# trade-off; just delete it.) Needs this .gitattributes present on both merged
# branches to take effect.
CLAUDE.md merge=union
